                        <a href="#story2" name="story2">DEMO DAY</a><br />
<span style="color:#ffcc00;">WHEN: Wednesday, May 2, 2012, 2:30PM – 6:30PM, including cocktail reception.<br />
WHERE: Norris Cinema Theatre, 900 W. 34th Street, Los Angeles, CA 90089</span><br /><br />
Students from across the School will demonstrate a host of games, hardware and interactive experiences. Demonstrations will include:<ul>
<li>Combiform: A new gaming console delivering a series of highly social games, transforming the players' focus back into the physical environment and onto social interactions.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/combiform">https://www.facebook.com/combiform</a></li>
<li>In Memory: Search your own fragmented mind for the answers that could save your daughter's life.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.fadefrommemory.com">http://www.fadefrommemory.com</a></li>
<li>Clockwork Zombies: Watchmaker Benjamin Salisbury steps up to the task of saving his home space colony from the evil Clockwork Zombies. Time is running out!<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.clockworkzombies.com">http://www.clockworkzombies.com</a></li>
<li>Nevermind: A psychological horror game that leverages biofeedback technology to detect fear and stress in the player.  Braving horrific scenarios and the menacing unknown, players must remain in control of their stress-induced impulses, as panicking will only make things worse.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.nevermindgame.com">http://www.nevermindgame.com</a></li>
<li>Tales from the Minus Lab: Harness the power to shrink and grow at will as you explore the uncharted worlds hidden within a single room.  Tales from the Minus Lab is a first-person adventure of ever-changing proportions.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.nevermindgame.com">http://www.nevermindgame.com</a></li>
<li>Blink: A third-person action-stealth game in which the player takes the role of Iris, a deadly saboteur who has gained the ability to teleport.  She must escape from dangerous weapons and a robotics facility, choosing to do so either by moving through the shadows or taking down all in her path using combat maneuvers with her newfound ability.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.blinkthegame.com">http://www.blinkthegame.com</a></li>
<li>Forestwalker: Use your iPad to lead a family of powerful heroes through the dark forest in search of their missing children.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://forestwalkerapp.com">http://forestwalkerapp.com</a></li></ul>
The program will be followed by a reception, during which students will conduct live demonstrations.
<br /><br />
Presenting students are enrolled in either the School of Cinematic Arts (B.A., Interactive Media; M.F.A., Interactive Media) or Viterbi School of Engineering (B.S., Computer Science - Games; M.S., Computer Science - Game Development; Ph.D., Computer Science - Games).  Concept art, 3D models, animation, rigging, music and sound for the games are provided by students across USC, as well as collaborative schools such as Laguna College of Art & Design and Atlantic College in Puerto Rico.
<br /><br />
CONTACT: Suzanne Wu, USC Media Relations<br />
		Kristin Borella, USC School of Cinematic Arts<br />
		Katie Dunham, USC Viterbi School of Engineering
<br />
