                        IMD FORUM<br />
<span style="color:#ffcc00;">Speaker:  Joseph Joy<br />
Time: 6-8pm<br />
Location: USC's Robert Zemeckis Center for Digital Arts (RZC), Room 122</span><br /><br />
The first 14 years of Joseph's professional career was in product development, mostly in the Microsoft Windows Operating System division, and working primarily in the area of clustering, networking and telephony. In 2005, after 14 years in Redmond, he joined  Microsoft Research India, where until November 2007 he headed the Advanced Development  (ADG) Group. He is now a software architect, driving the RIN project. His primary interests are in multimedia storytelling, software engineering and semi-structured information retrieval. His personal page lists other interests.  He has a Certificate in independent filmmaking from University of Washington, an MS in Computer Science and a 2nd MS in Ocean Engineering, both from the University of New Hampshire, and a B. Tech. in Naval Archiecture from the Indian Institute of Technology, Madras.   He will discuss his work on recent projects: Rich Interactive Narratives (RIN, see also www.digitalnarratives.net) and Virtual India (now Digital Heritage).<br />
